WEBVTT

00:07.907 --> 00:10.068
How are you today?
Do you see anything you like?

00:10.143 --> 00:13.510
Uh, is Dennis here?
He usually takes care of me.

00:13.580 --> 00:16.481
Oh, no, I'm afraid Dennis quit.
He quit?

00:16.549 --> 00:20.610
Yeah, apparently he had one
regular customer that was
driving him crazy.

00:20.687 --> 00:23.622
Now we're gonna be up all night
wondering who that was.

00:23.690 --> 00:26.921
Can I help you?
[Inhales]

00:26.993 --> 00:31.760
Dennis quit.
Yes, we are looking for another
shirt just like this.

00:31.831 --> 00:34.197
Y-You want the same shirt?
Identical, yeah.

00:34.267 --> 00:37.828
Same color, same pattern.
16-inch neck, 33-inch sleeve.

00:37.904 --> 00:42.068
Okay, but you already have one
of those, so, um, maybe it's
time to try a little variety-

00:42.142 --> 00:44.406
<i>[Natalie Clears Throat]</i>
Because-

00:44.477 --> 00:46.604
Or maybe not.

00:46.679 --> 00:50.547
Okay, um, uh, yeah.
Here you go.

00:50.617 --> 00:52.608
16-inch collar, 33 sleeve.

00:52.685 --> 00:54.812
[Sighs]

00:54.888 --> 00:58.517
No, yeah, this, uh, this was
inspected by Number 6.

00:58.591 --> 01:02.584
I'm not a big fan of Number 6.
Do you have any that are
inspected by Number 8?

01:02.662 --> 01:05.654
[Chuckles]
You're kidding, right?

01:05.732 --> 01:08.360
You're-You're not kidding.

01:08.435 --> 01:10.903
Okay, um, the customer's
always right.

01:10.970 --> 01:14.997
[Whispering]
At least until today.

01:15.075 --> 01:20.342
Um, Number 5, Number 2.
Okay, here you go.

01:20.413 --> 01:24.645
<i>Inspected by Number 8.</i>
Ah! There it is.

01:24.717 --> 01:26.810
Is- Is there really a difference?

01:26.886 --> 01:30.049
Are you kidding?
Look at this.

01:30.123 --> 01:32.523
Look, she's an artist.

01:32.592 --> 01:35.186
Oh, I've been admiring
her work for years.

01:35.261 --> 01:38.992
You know, every shirt, every stitch,

01:39.065 --> 01:41.329
every button is perfect.

01:41.401 --> 01:43.665
There's a tear.
There's a tear.
Where, where, where?

01:43.736 --> 01:47.729
There's a tear, right there.
[Sighs] And look at this.

01:47.807 --> 01:50.207
This sleeve is all wrong.
It's completely crooked.

01:50.276 --> 01:54.007
Well, maybe she had a bad day.
No, that's not possible.

01:54.080 --> 01:57.072
I know Inspector Number 8.

01:57.150 --> 01:59.141
She never lets anything
get past her.

02:05.024 --> 02:07.015
Mr. Monk, are you okay?

02:07.093 --> 02:12.087
Natalie, something's wrong.
What?

02:12.165 --> 02:14.690
Something is very wrong
with Inspector Number 8.

02:20.206 --> 02:22.265
Dennis?

02:24.177 --> 02:26.668
Dennis!

02:28.000 --> 02:34.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:49.469 --> 02:52.666
[Sobs]

02:56.476 --> 02:59.138
[Sobbing]

03:00.413 --> 03:03.541
<i>## [Up-tempo Folk]</i>

03:03.616 --> 03:05.550
<i># It's a jungle out there #</i>

03:05.618 --> 03:09.349
<i># Disorder and confusion</i>
<i>everywhere #</i>

03:10.423 --> 03:12.789
<i># No one seems to care #</i>

03:12.859 --> 03:16.955
<i># Well, I do</i>
<i>Hey, who's in charge here #</i>

03:17.030 --> 03:19.863
<i># It's a jungle out there #</i>

03:19.933 --> 03:23.630
<i># Poison in the very air</i>
<i>we breathe #</i>

03:23.703 --> 03:27.070
<i># Do you know what's in the water</i>
<i>that you drink, well, I do #</i>

03:27.140 --> 03:30.303
<i># And it's amazing #</i>

03:30.376 --> 03:33.539
<i># People think I'm crazy</i>
<i>'cause I worry all the time #</i>

03:33.613 --> 03:35.740
<i># If you paid attention</i>
<i>you'd be worried too #</i>

03:37.150 --> 03:40.950
<i># You better pay attention</i>
<i>or this world we love so much #</i>

03:41.020 --> 03:44.751
<i># Mightjust kill you #</i>

03:44.824 --> 03:47.657
<i># I could be wrong now #</i>

03:47.727 --> 03:49.718
<i># But I don't think so #</i>

03:49.796 --> 03:51.491
<i># 'Cause it's a jungle out there #</i>

03:51.564 --> 03:54.089
<i># It's a jungle out there ##</i>

03:57.971 --> 04:01.805
<i>[Camera Shutters Clicking]</i>
Mrs. Hammond, I need
to hear this again, please.

04:01.874 --> 04:05.207
Now, you came home and you
found your husband on the floor
about an hour ago.

04:05.278 --> 04:07.269
Yes.
And he'd been stabbed.

04:07.347 --> 04:09.406
- Yes.
- It's not funny.

04:09.482 --> 04:11.450
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.
It's not funny.

04:11.517 --> 04:15.112
Inspector Number 8 was very
important to me because no
matter how bad things got,

04:15.188 --> 04:17.349
I knew I could
always count on her.

04:17.423 --> 04:20.392
Mr. Monk, you understand
you're talking about someone
you have never even met...

04:20.459 --> 04:23.327
who works in a factory somewhere
who inspects shirts!

04:23.396 --> 04:26.331
She's my soul mate.
You don't even know
if it's a man or a woman.

04:26.399 --> 04:29.527
I love her.
I think she's in trouble.

04:29.602 --> 04:32.400
Okay, maybe she's retired.
Maybe there's a new Number 8.

04:32.472 --> 04:34.463
No, it's not possible.

04:34.540 --> 04:36.667
She would never retire.
She loves her work.

04:36.743 --> 04:38.677
Look at this shirt.
Now, Inspector Number 5,

04:38.745 --> 04:41.737
I can see him retiring
because he stopped caring years ago.

04:41.814 --> 04:43.805
Monk.
What?

04:43.883 --> 04:45.874
They're about to take the body
away. Wanna come have a look?

04:45.952 --> 04:48.216
I'll be right there!
I've only got five shirts left.

04:48.288 --> 04:51.223
Wh-Wh-What if I spill something?
What if one rips?

04:51.291 --> 04:53.623
What's up?
[Monk] It's like an
endangered species now.

04:53.693 --> 04:55.684
He's obsessing over shirts.

04:55.762 --> 04:57.855
Look, put two shirts
in the dryer.
Yeah?

04:57.930 --> 05:00.364
Close the door.
See if they mate.

05:00.433 --> 05:03.129
Hey, Monk?
What?

05:03.202 --> 05:05.193
What do you think?
About what?

05:05.271 --> 05:07.671
About the dead guy
in the kitchen.
Oh, yeah. I'm sorry.

05:07.740 --> 05:09.674
I was thinking about
something else.

05:09.742 --> 05:14.441
He's worried about the woman
who inspects his shirts.
I've been to three different stores.

05:14.514 --> 05:17.608
Captain, the stitching, i-i-it's all-
It's all wrong.

05:17.684 --> 05:20.517
The collars are crooked-
Okay, Captain,
just please fill us in.

05:20.586 --> 05:22.577
Okay, they're both
classical musicians.

05:22.655 --> 05:25.715
They got married about
six months ago.
It's just not like her.

05:25.792 --> 05:28.886
The wife was down at the
rehearsal studio practicing her cello.

05:28.961 --> 05:32.658
She comes home 3:30,
she finds her husband dead
on the kitchen floor,

05:32.732 --> 05:35.667
room temperature,
stabbed three times.

05:35.735 --> 05:39.796
Well, she's lying.
She wasn't practicing.

05:39.872 --> 05:42.932
You can't play the cello wearing
a long skirt like that.
You know what I'm gonna do?

05:43.009 --> 05:45.671
I'm gonna find Inspector 8.
I'm gonna track her down.

05:45.745 --> 05:49.511
Shirt factory's in Rockaway.
That's two hours from here.

05:49.582 --> 05:51.573
I think he's right.
Yeah. Take her downtown.

05:51.651 --> 05:53.778
[Chuckles]
Hey, Monk.

05:53.853 --> 05:56.083
Thank you.
For what?

05:56.155 --> 05:58.783
- You solved the case.
- Oh, yeah, sure.

05:58.858 --> 06:01.258
If she is in trouble,
maybe I can help her.

06:01.327 --> 06:05.661
That's Number 4.
He's a hack.

06:05.732 --> 06:08.394
He makes Inspector Number 10
look like Inspector Number 6.

06:08.468 --> 06:10.959
<i>[Man On P.A.]</i>
<i>Maria, line one. Maria.</i>

06:11.037 --> 06:14.734
Hi. [Aside] 6.

06:16.342 --> 06:18.503
There she is.
There she is.

06:18.578 --> 06:20.705
That's her.
That's Number 8.

06:20.780 --> 06:22.873
Well, are you gonna ask her out?

06:22.949 --> 06:26.282
No, I'm just, um- I'm nervous.

06:26.352 --> 06:28.752
Okay, go on. Go on.

06:32.859 --> 06:35.657
Excuse me,
[Voice Quivers] Number 8?

06:35.728 --> 06:38.561
[Sighs]
I'm Adrian Monk.

06:38.631 --> 06:43.125
This is my friend, Natalie Teeger.
Adrian Monk?
The same?

06:43.202 --> 06:47.298
<i>[Monk]</i>
<i>Oh, you saved it.!</i>
<i>That's the only fan letter I ever wrote.</i>

06:47.373 --> 06:50.638
I am Maria Ortiz.

06:50.710 --> 06:53.679
Maria, it's an honor
and a pleasure.

06:53.746 --> 06:58.445
It's so nice when you can put
a face with the-the little tag
in the pocket.

06:59.786 --> 07:03.051
Uh-oh.
Are you approving this?

07:03.122 --> 07:05.784
Th-Th-This has a little-
little stain there.

07:09.662 --> 07:12.495
I knew it. I knew it.
[Sobs]

07:12.565 --> 07:16.501
You are upset about something.
Maria, Mr. Monk has been
really worried about you.

07:16.569 --> 07:20.437
It's not me.
It's my son, Pablo.

07:20.506 --> 07:22.974
Oh, I remember this case.

07:23.042 --> 07:27.809
The model, Clea Vance.
<i>The papers are wrong.</i>
<i>Everyone is wrong.</i>

07:27.880 --> 07:30.644
Pablo is a good boy.
He's innocent.

07:30.716 --> 07:33.514
Oh! I know it's hard.

07:33.586 --> 07:37.454
You might feel better if you
focused on your work,

07:37.523 --> 07:41.857
you know, and started
inspecting these shirts again.

07:43.162 --> 07:47.098
[Sighs]
Here's the thing, Maria. Um-

07:47.166 --> 07:49.225
I've, uh- I've only got
five shirts left.

07:49.302 --> 07:51.361
Mr. Monk. Mr. Monk.
You can help her.

07:51.437 --> 07:53.632
Yes. Uh, Maria, Mr. Monk
is a detective.

07:53.706 --> 07:55.697
He's-He's a great detective.
He's famous.

07:55.775 --> 07:58.335
And you came here to help my boy?

07:58.411 --> 08:02.404
Um, well, no, actually.

08:02.482 --> 08:05.940
My, uh- My first priority
really is, uh,

08:06.018 --> 08:08.384
to get you to focus again,
you know, because,

08:08.454 --> 08:10.752
um, the shirts, Maria-

08:10.823 --> 08:15.226
Mr. Monk, I have been praying for
such a one as you to help me-

08:15.294 --> 08:17.888
Great.
Pablo is innocent.

08:17.964 --> 08:21.456
When you talk to him,
you will see.
Whoa, when I talk to him?

08:21.534 --> 08:24.867
Uh, no.
L-l-l-l-l-I never agreed.

08:24.937 --> 08:28.065
[Sobbing]
<i>Oh, my gosh.</i>

08:28.140 --> 08:31.701
Oh, Maria,
I'm so sorry, sweetie.

08:31.777 --> 08:34.143
Stop it.

08:38.751 --> 08:42.551
How did this happen?
How do you talk me
into these things?

08:42.621 --> 08:45.785
Because it's the right
thing to do.
Have you read this?

08:45.858 --> 08:48.656
Look at-
There are witnesses.
There's D.N.A. Evidence.

08:48.728 --> 08:51.822
Natalie, he did it.
There's no doubt about it.

08:51.898 --> 08:53.889
Well, it doesn't hurt
to meet him.

08:53.966 --> 08:57.868
<i>[Buzzer Buzzes]</i>
If I go back to Maria and tell
her that her son <i>is</i> guilty,

08:57.937 --> 09:02.397
she'll completely fall apart,
which would be worse
because I am down to five shirts.

09:07.346 --> 09:11.942
- Mr. Monk. Miss Teeger?
- Yes.

09:12.018 --> 09:14.816
L-I talked to my mother.
She told me you were coming.

09:20.026 --> 09:24.463
How do you know my mother?
From her work at the factory.
I'm a big fan.

09:24.530 --> 09:28.557
- A fan?
- Pablo, your mother asked
that we look into your case.

09:28.634 --> 09:32.832
- We'd like to hear your side.
- I did not kill Clea Vance.
That is my side.

09:32.905 --> 09:36.102
I never met her.
I never see her.

09:36.175 --> 09:39.303
There was a fashion show
at a big hotel. I was a delivery boy.

09:39.378 --> 09:42.279
I delivered some clothes there,
then I go home.

09:42.348 --> 09:44.816
The next day, I'm arrested.

09:44.884 --> 09:48.149
[Sighs, Speaks Spanish]

09:48.220 --> 09:50.586
"It is a nightmare."

09:50.656 --> 09:53.454
Pablo, your D.N.A.
Was all over the victim.

09:53.526 --> 09:55.619
Your blood.
Your hair.

09:55.695 --> 09:57.822
How do you explain that?

09:57.897 --> 10:00.593
[Sighs]

10:00.666 --> 10:02.827
I don't know.

10:02.902 --> 10:06.531
It's a mistake.

10:06.606 --> 10:09.166
Uh, a misunderstanding?

10:13.946 --> 10:19.282
Clea Vance had a roommate who
testified that Clea was afraid of you.

10:20.686 --> 10:23.655
She says that you were
stalking her.

10:23.723 --> 10:26.556
Look. It says right here,

10:26.626 --> 10:29.857
"Pablo Ortiz was obsessed with her."

10:29.929 --> 10:33.365
You see that, right there?

10:35.868 --> 10:38.393
I see it.

10:38.471 --> 10:41.963
You're lying, Pablo.
It doesn't say that.

10:44.276 --> 10:46.710
You can't read English, can you?

10:46.779 --> 10:52.376
No, sir. I was raised
in Mexico with my father.

10:52.451 --> 10:54.817
I have been here 3 years only,

10:54.887 --> 10:58.914
and I can speak English, but...

10:58.991 --> 11:00.982
I cannot read.

11:01.060 --> 11:03.187
[Sighs]

11:11.704 --> 11:13.865
What is it?

11:17.043 --> 11:19.739
- That's an emergency exit.
- <i>Yeah?</i>

11:19.812 --> 11:21.905
Well, the killer didn't use it.

11:21.981 --> 11:25.348
According to this floor plan,

11:25.418 --> 11:28.683
he would have had to go all the way
around back through the kitchen.

11:28.754 --> 11:30.949
It was crowded.
It was risky.

11:31.023 --> 11:34.789
Somebody could have seen him.
Yeah, but he wouldn't use it.
The alarm would sound.

11:34.860 --> 11:39.229
Exactly. Whoever killed
this woman read that sign.

11:40.332 --> 11:43.130
And Pablo can't read.

11:46.439 --> 11:49.636
Do you think he's innocent?
You do, don't you?

11:57.717 --> 12:01.744
The dead model, right?
I remember this case.
I did the work on this one myself.

12:01.821 --> 12:05.154
- Is there any new evidence?
- No. Monk met the killer's mother.

12:05.224 --> 12:08.421
- She's a shirt inspector.
- She swears he's innocent.

12:08.494 --> 12:12.328
Oh, I know. That's the hardest
part of the job, the mother's crying
and pleading.

12:12.398 --> 12:14.593
- That's one thing
I'm not gonna miss.
- Where are you going?

12:14.667 --> 12:16.658
Didn't you hear?
I'm retiring.

12:16.736 --> 12:18.727
There's a party for me on Friday
if you wanna come.

12:18.804 --> 12:21.568
Cool. Absolutely. I'm there.
You're retiring?
How old are you?

12:21.640 --> 12:24.370
46.
Did you win the lottery?

12:24.443 --> 12:26.434
No, I've been investing,
real estate.

12:26.512 --> 12:30.141
- What have you been doing
with your savings?
- Uh, eating.

12:30.216 --> 12:32.480
You know, I need to talk
to my accountant.

12:32.551 --> 12:35.281
Wait, you have an accountant?
Nope, gonna have
to get an accountant.

12:35.354 --> 12:38.790
- Then I'm gonna talk to him.
- There's something wrong
with this picture.

12:38.858 --> 12:42.817
- What?
- I don't know. Something.

12:42.895 --> 12:45.489
<i>So these are her shoes?</i>

12:45.564 --> 12:49.796
That's right. Yeah, you see
this blood and this hair
and these fibers?

12:49.869 --> 12:52.269
They all belong to Pablo Ortiz.
It's a slam dunk.

12:52.338 --> 12:56.297
Yeah, I don't see any wiggle
room here, do you?
No, we got the right man.

12:56.375 --> 13:00.641
People lie.
People lie all the time,
but D.N.A.? It never lies.

13:00.713 --> 13:03.841
I'm thinking- I'm thinking
maybe he's not the guy.

13:03.916 --> 13:07.477
- Yeah, see, there's this exit door-
- Look, I heard about the exit door.

13:07.553 --> 13:10.113
- It's right there.
- Look, Monk, I'd follow you
anywhere...

13:10.189 --> 13:13.022
but I've got 4 cases on
my plate right now.

13:13.092 --> 13:16.027
But you have fun.
Knock yourself out.
Thanks, Gordo.

13:16.095 --> 13:20.657
See you at the party.
Here's the statement from that
Natasia Zorelle.

13:20.733 --> 13:23.224
She was the victim's roommate.
Let's start with her.

13:23.302 --> 13:27.068
Did you just say you were, uh,
gonna go and talk with Natasia Zorelle?

13:27.139 --> 13:30.631
- The supermodel?
- Is that her?

13:30.709 --> 13:33.735
Yeah, actually, I've got
the rest of the day off.

13:33.813 --> 13:37.943
- I should probably go with you guys.
- You know, I think I'll come
along too, in the interest of, uh-

13:38.017 --> 13:40.850
Justice?
Yeah, justice.

13:40.920 --> 13:43.081
[Camera Shutters Clicking]

13:43.155 --> 13:46.147
Get a close up.
Come on, Michael.

14:00.072 --> 14:04.600
They all look so unhappy.
How can you be that attractive
and be so sad?

14:04.677 --> 14:08.738
Well, maybe it's because we're
never really sure if people like
us for ourselves.

14:10.115 --> 14:12.345
No, what's this?
No! No, no, no!

14:12.418 --> 14:15.285
That's not what I asked for!
Look!

14:15.354 --> 14:18.846
Look, the collar has to
flare like this.

14:18.924 --> 14:21.791
- Huh? Do you see?
- Julian, they just painted that.

14:21.861 --> 14:24.557
Hmm?
She's an animal.

14:24.630 --> 14:28.691
She's in heat. Huh? Good.
You, what do you think?

14:28.767 --> 14:32.863
- Uh, I like it.
- You like it.

14:32.938 --> 14:36.931
What's that supposed to mean?
Say you love it or say you hate it!

14:37.009 --> 14:41.105
Anything in between is pointless.
Wet One, Wet One, Wet One.

14:41.180 --> 14:44.707
<i>Come on. Thank you.</i>

14:44.783 --> 14:48.116
<i>You, blue shirt.!</i>
<i>Are you here to audition?</i>

14:48.187 --> 14:50.314
Me? No.

14:50.389 --> 14:53.586
Well, you may want to consider it.
I like your attitude.

14:58.497 --> 15:00.590
Hello.

15:07.706 --> 15:11.335
If you're gonna rob me,
you should bring a gun.
Pardon me?

15:11.410 --> 15:13.401
The blouse.

15:13.479 --> 15:16.107
It's a knockoff
of one of my designs.

15:16.181 --> 15:18.240
Oh, it is?
I didn't know.
Of course.

15:18.317 --> 15:22.777
That's not the real crime.
The real crime is how you look in it.

15:22.855 --> 15:25.949
<i>[Woman]</i>
<i>Julian, you're booked in Milan</i>
<i>the day after the show.</i>

15:26.025 --> 15:28.255
Okay. Okay.
The girls are here. You said
you wanted fresh faces.

15:28.327 --> 15:30.591
- Good. Good. No, darling.
- He did it.

15:30.663 --> 15:33.655
Natalie, he's not
even a suspect.
Damn!

15:33.732 --> 15:36.530
No. Turn around.
Not this time.

15:36.602 --> 15:40.538
Next time. Oh! Mmm!

15:40.606 --> 15:43.473
Yes, yes. You're perfect.
What's your name?

15:43.542 --> 15:48.070
Sarah.
Sarah. Heaven must
be missing one of its angels.

15:48.147 --> 15:50.741
Excuse me.
Sorry, um-
What?

15:50.816 --> 15:56.049
Well, it's nothing.
It's just, uh, those eyebrows
aren't gonna look so good-

15:56.121 --> 16:00.649
- Which one?
- Well, the left one's higher than
the right one, isn't it?

16:02.361 --> 16:07.458
Oh. This eyebrow is a little bit
lower than that one.

16:07.533 --> 16:11.401
Oh, maybe next time, Sarah.
Yeah.

16:11.470 --> 16:14.166
Thanks for coming in.

16:14.239 --> 16:16.537
Who are you?
I'm Adrian Monk.

16:16.608 --> 16:20.044
I'm with
the San Francisco Police.

16:20.112 --> 16:23.047
Yeah, we're, uh-we're looking
for Natasia Zorelle.

16:23.115 --> 16:26.380
Well, she's working.
Oh, and do me a favor.

16:26.452 --> 16:30.013
Don't arrest her
until after the show.
She hasn't done anything.

16:30.089 --> 16:33.058
We're actually looking
into the murder of Clea Vance.

16:33.125 --> 16:37.289
Well, why? Isn't that old news?
I thought the killer
was in jail somewhere.

16:37.363 --> 16:40.127
I mean, don't you people read
the newspapers?

16:40.199 --> 16:42.292
Did you know her?

16:42.368 --> 16:46.099
I know every model in California
and every wannabe.

16:46.171 --> 16:49.436
Clea was a...
should-not-have-been.

16:49.508 --> 16:53.205
You know, she showed up
wasted to my last show.
Almost ruined me.

16:53.278 --> 16:55.906
Now, let that be a lesson
to you girls.

16:55.981 --> 17:00.008
She ruined my last show
and two hours later,
the delivery boy killed her.

17:00.085 --> 17:04.214
- And I kid you not.
- We'd still like to talk to Natasia.

17:04.289 --> 17:07.258
She's at the beach.
We are shooting our new
catalog.

17:07.326 --> 17:11.285
Listen, I've gotta be there very soon,
so you can follow me if you like.

17:11.363 --> 17:13.593
All right, girls. Good.
All right.

17:13.665 --> 17:16.964
I'll meet you there.
I gotta go pick upJulie...
and change.

17:19.137 --> 17:22.130
Okay, that's it. That's what I need.
Keep it going.

17:22.207 --> 17:24.573
<i>Sell it. Sell it.</i>
<i>There we go.</i>

17:24.643 --> 17:27.271
<i>Again. Good.</i>

17:27.346 --> 17:30.611
Sell it. Sell it.
Good. Sell it.

17:33.619 --> 17:36.918
Sweetie, just stay right here,
okay? I'll be back.

17:53.872 --> 17:57.433
What are you doing?
What?

17:57.509 --> 18:02.242
I'm standing.
This is how I stand.

18:02.314 --> 18:04.305
What are you wearing?
Clothes.

18:04.383 --> 18:06.374
This is how I dress.
This is how I stand.

18:06.452 --> 18:08.443
This is how I dress.

18:20.999 --> 18:23.661
Excuse me,
would you put that out?
It's bothering me.

18:23.735 --> 18:28.001
But you're smoking.
My smoke isn't bothering me.

18:28.073 --> 18:31.270
Hmm? Thank you.
All right.

18:31.343 --> 18:33.777
She'll talk to you,
but make it quick.

18:33.846 --> 18:37.509
I'm not paying her a thousand
dollars an hour just to chat.
Uh, thank you.

18:37.583 --> 18:39.710
Can you give us a minute?
Sure. All right, everybody.

18:39.785 --> 18:41.878
<i>Take ten. Let's get her</i>
<i>in the other dress, please.</i>

18:41.954 --> 18:44.889
Sweetheart, oh,
you look ravishing.

18:44.957 --> 18:48.757
These gentlemen are from the
police department. They want
to talk to you about Clea Vance.

18:48.827 --> 18:50.818
Why?
We're not sure.

18:50.896 --> 18:54.297
Probably just tilting
at windmills.
Windmills?

18:54.366 --> 18:59.770
Mm. It's a literary reference...
from a book.

19:01.039 --> 19:03.371
Um, I guess I can talk while I
change.

19:05.010 --> 19:07.478
Meet me over there?

19:11.583 --> 19:14.211
Only one of you.

19:15.554 --> 19:19.354
Okay. I guess the only fair way
is, uh, alphabetically.

19:19.424 --> 19:23.053
Oh, Adrian.
Last names.

19:23.128 --> 19:25.619
So "A" is no.
Uh, "B", no, "C", no.

19:25.697 --> 19:28.996
"D", Disher, that's-
Monk, you go.
It's your case.

19:33.539 --> 19:36.099
Disher comes before Monk.
It's the first last name.

19:39.811 --> 19:41.836
What are you,
in mourning for your life?

19:46.084 --> 19:48.416
Yeah, I got it.
We're comin' in.

19:49.922 --> 19:52.618
You were Clea's roommate?

19:52.691 --> 19:55.683
Yeah, and best friend.
I see.

19:55.761 --> 19:57.752
I see.

19:57.829 --> 20:01.230
I see. Uh! Oh!
Oh! Whoa, whoa, oh, whoa.

20:01.300 --> 20:04.599
Oh, whoa.
That's okay. I'm not shy.

20:04.670 --> 20:09.903
- You have, uh-you have something
on your shoulder.
- Oh, it's a mole. It's my trademark.

20:09.975 --> 20:14.309
Yeah, did-did-did you know
Pablo, uh, Ortiz?

20:14.379 --> 20:17.405
I didn't know him, except that
Clea was terrified of him.

20:17.482 --> 20:21.578
He was stalking her.
Yes, there-
there's no evidence of that.

20:21.653 --> 20:25.953
No phone calls.
No other moles-
I mean, witnesses.

20:26.024 --> 20:29.391
No other witnesses.
Are you saying I made it all up?

20:29.461 --> 20:31.827
Um-
Why would I do that?

20:31.897 --> 20:34.627
I don't know.
Look, I saw what I saw.
He brought her flowers.

20:34.700 --> 20:38.101
He hit on her.
I already testified about all
this a year ago.

20:38.170 --> 20:40.934
I read your statement.
Then read it again.

20:41.006 --> 20:44.407
Okay.

20:44.476 --> 20:47.104
What are you doing?

20:47.179 --> 20:52.173
If you put one on this side,
you know, y-you'd be perfect.

20:52.251 --> 20:54.651
Y-Your career would-
[Makes Flying Sound]

20:54.720 --> 20:56.915
Do you have
any more questions?

20:56.989 --> 20:59.958
No.
Good.

21:00.025 --> 21:02.459
'Cause I got to get back to work.

21:05.764 --> 21:07.755
Hey.
Hi, there.

21:09.701 --> 21:12.864
How'd it go?
She's hot.

21:12.938 --> 21:15.168
Uh, she's mildly irritated.

21:15.240 --> 21:17.640
<i>[Monk Sighs]</i>
<i>Give her a minute.</i>

21:17.709 --> 21:20.701
She'll calm down.

21:22.748 --> 21:24.978
<i>[Man]</i>
<i>All right, great.</i>
<i>You look beautiful.</i>

21:25.050 --> 21:27.041
<i>Keep going. Great.</i>

21:27.119 --> 21:30.145
Hi. Mom, I got bored.
Sweetie.

21:30.222 --> 21:33.316
Please, can I stay?
I won't say anything.
Shh, shh, shh. Watch.

21:36.028 --> 21:38.997
Mom, that man's looking at me.
[Camera Shutter Clicks]

21:39.064 --> 21:41.123
What's he doing?
I don't know.

21:41.199 --> 21:43.497
<i>Mr. Hodge?</i>
Who is she?

21:43.568 --> 21:45.968
Who are you?
This is my daughter, Julie.

21:46.038 --> 21:48.905
This is Mr. Hodge.
Let me see you walk.

21:48.974 --> 21:52.239
Why?
Because lighting may be striking.

21:52.311 --> 21:55.610
Your life may be changing.
Now, just walk over there.

21:55.681 --> 21:58.149
Come on.

21:58.216 --> 22:01.185
That's it, good. Turn around.
[Camera Shutter Clicking]

22:01.253 --> 22:04.086
- <i>Hold your head up.</i>
<i>Smile. Come back.</i>
- [Camera Shutter Clicking]

22:04.156 --> 22:06.681
Good.
I want you to model for me.

22:06.758 --> 22:10.091
You can be in the show
on Thursday night. Hmm?

22:10.162 --> 22:12.528
You know,
you could be a big star.

22:12.597 --> 22:15.725
Great and wonderful things.
Oh, my God!

22:15.801 --> 22:19.066
No, she's 13 years old.
I've had models
younger than that.

22:19.137 --> 22:22.595
Thirteen? She's practically middle-aged.
Thank you. I don't think so.

22:22.674 --> 22:27.509
Anyway, it's not up to you.
This is between Julie
and her biological mother.

22:27.579 --> 22:31.606
I <i>am</i> her biological mother.
Oh.

22:31.683 --> 22:34.811
[Camera Shutter Clicks]
[Sighs]

22:34.886 --> 22:38.014
Mom.
No.

22:41.860 --> 22:44.294
Sweetie, come on.
It's gonna get cold.

22:55.307 --> 22:58.902
Are you wearing makeup?
I told you, not until you're 18.

22:58.977 --> 23:02.811
Mom, when I'm 18,
I'll be too late.
I really wanna do this.

23:02.881 --> 23:07.545
You know, a lot of these girls
have serious problems, okay?
Drugs and eating disorders.

23:07.619 --> 23:12.215
It's just one show, and if you're
right and I hate it, I'll quit.

23:13.992 --> 23:19.225
But at least I'll have tried.
You always tell me to try to new things.

23:21.400 --> 23:23.561
Forget modeling.
You should be a lawyer.

23:23.635 --> 23:26.229
Is that a "yes"?

23:26.304 --> 23:29.432
I'm gonna be with you
the whole time.

23:29.508 --> 23:32.443
Wow! I'm modeling
forJulian Hodge.

23:32.511 --> 23:37.574
Isn't he wonderful?
That's not exactly the word
I would have used.

23:37.649 --> 23:41.210
<i>[Knocking]</i>

23:41.286 --> 23:43.584
Oh. Julian.

23:43.655 --> 23:46.180
Hi.

23:46.258 --> 23:48.249
[Kisses]
Hey.

23:48.326 --> 23:51.352
You surprised?
Not after today.

23:51.430 --> 23:54.058
I figured you might
be freaking out.

23:54.132 --> 23:57.533
Do they know anything?
I don't think so.

23:57.602 --> 23:59.593
You're not smoking.
No.

23:59.671 --> 24:04.165
No, uh, you know, cigarettes,
they tend to leave a nasty odor.

24:06.445 --> 24:09.710
I wouldn't want them
to know I was here.
Who?

24:12.484 --> 24:15.817
The police.
Oh, I didn't tell them anything.

24:17.889 --> 24:21.416
But you will... eventually.

24:21.493 --> 24:23.825
But-
Shh, shh, shh!

24:25.030 --> 24:30.229
It's not your fault, my darling.
You're just too pretty.

24:30.302 --> 24:33.169
And beauty like yours,
a face like this-

24:33.238 --> 24:35.502
Shh.

24:37.909 --> 24:40.503
You just wouldn't
be able to take the pressure.

24:53.225 --> 24:58.822
[No Audible Dialogue]

25:17.682 --> 25:19.912
How's it look, Gordo?
Well, it looks like suicide,

25:19.985 --> 25:21.976
smells like suicide.

25:22.053 --> 25:27.286
Smart money's on suicide.
She drained two of those bottles
and maybe 30 sleeping pills.

25:27.359 --> 25:30.192
Were those prescription?
Probably not.

25:30.262 --> 25:32.253
We'll check with her doctor.
Make a note.

25:32.330 --> 25:35.766
I'll remember.
Where's your notebook?

25:35.834 --> 25:39.634
I didn't bring it.
It's an Italian suit.
It was ruining the lines.

25:39.704 --> 25:42.764
Don't worry. [Clicks Tongue]
I got it.

25:42.841 --> 25:45.833
Am I in your way?

25:48.213 --> 25:50.374
She probably got depressed
after you spoke to her.

25:50.448 --> 25:52.882
- All those memories
about the murder bubbling up.
- I don't think so.

25:52.951 --> 25:56.910
One set of fingerprints
on the glass.
Yeah, they're hers.

25:56.988 --> 25:59.422
But, look, she's wearing lipstick.

25:59.491 --> 26:02.983
There's no lipstick on the glass.

26:03.061 --> 26:05.427
Somebody wiped down the glass...

26:05.497 --> 26:08.295
and then put it back in her hand.

26:08.366 --> 26:13.394
Okay, this is now a homicide
investigation!

26:13.471 --> 26:16.497
Lock this joint down.
Nobody touches anything.

26:16.575 --> 26:20.773
<i>Fabio, go and borrow a notebook</i>
<i>and borrow a pencil and start</i>
<i>talking to neighbors.</i>

26:20.845 --> 26:23.439
[Natalie]
Captain, what do you
think it means?

26:23.515 --> 26:25.949
It means that your boss scared
somebody.

26:36.695 --> 26:39.163
Rest in peace.

26:43.935 --> 26:46.768
<i>[Man On P.A.]</i>
<i>Ladies and gentlemen, rehearsals</i>
<i>up in ten minutes.</i>

26:46.838 --> 26:50.069
<i>Please take your places.</i>
<i>Final touches.</i>

26:50.141 --> 26:53.338
Oh, she looks beautiful,
doesn't she?

26:53.411 --> 26:55.402
[Sighs]
Too beautiful.

26:55.480 --> 26:58.210
Sometimes I wish she had a big
old fat hairy wart right here.

26:58.283 --> 27:00.717
Or maybe- maybe here.

27:00.785 --> 27:03.618
Everyone, um, could you just come
around here for a moment please?

27:03.688 --> 27:06.213
Thank you. Yes, put that down.
That's okay. Do that later.

27:06.291 --> 27:10.284
Thank you. I just want to say
a few quick words.

27:12.964 --> 27:14.989
This has been a terrible day
for us today.

27:15.066 --> 27:20.060
<i>As you know, last night</i>
<i>we lost a dear, dear friend.</i>

27:20.138 --> 27:23.665
And I know all of you here,
everyone,

27:23.742 --> 27:26.802
how much we loved Natasia,

27:26.878 --> 27:31.212
<i>except, of course,</i>
<i>when she was driving us nuts.</i>
<i>[Laughs]</i>

27:31.282 --> 27:33.876
But I can feel her here.

27:33.952 --> 27:37.547
<i>L- l-I can feel her spirit,</i>
<i>her soul.</i>

27:37.622 --> 27:43.390
Can you feel that? And I know
she's going to be with us
tomorrow night at the show.

27:43.461 --> 27:47.795
So let's not let her down.
Huh?

27:47.866 --> 27:49.925
Good.

27:50.001 --> 27:54.267
[Kisses]
This one's for you, baby.

27:54.339 --> 27:57.740
[Women Sigh]
Great. Thank you.

28:00.845 --> 28:04.975
<i>## [House]</i>

28:14.859 --> 28:17.623
You may want to change
the earrings.

28:30.809 --> 28:33.801
<i>## [Continues]</i>

28:38.316 --> 28:40.250
Look, look, look, look.

28:44.689 --> 28:48.557
<i>[Julian]</i>
<i>I knew you'd say that. Make a note.</i>
<i>Just change those earrings.</i>

28:48.626 --> 28:52.323
Cut! Cut! Cut, cut, cut!

28:52.397 --> 28:56.663
<i>Cut, cut, cut.</i>
<i>Julie, Julie, Julie.</i>

28:56.735 --> 29:00.136
Have you forgot something? Huh?
What?

29:00.205 --> 29:03.834
Have you forgot that when it
comes to my art, I'm a total monster?

29:03.908 --> 29:06.570
I mean, just look at yourself.
Look. You're a mess.

29:06.644 --> 29:09.841
I mean, look here.
Look at this. Look at the collar.

29:09.914 --> 29:13.475
Look, it's all twisted.
And-And-And all these wrinkles
on the dress.

29:13.551 --> 29:17.282
<i>I mean, look, sweetheart.</i>
Natalie, do you have
the case file?

29:17.355 --> 29:19.823
What?
The case file. Give it to me.

29:19.891 --> 29:24.487
<i>I'd rather put you in a burlap</i>
<i>bag than have you seen wearing</i>
<i>my clothes like this.</i>

29:24.562 --> 29:26.792
I knew something was wrong.
Look at this.

29:26.865 --> 29:29.993
Her body is all contorted.

29:30.068 --> 29:33.765
But the collar and her buttons
are perfectly straight.

29:33.838 --> 29:36.830
After he killed her,
he straightened them out.

29:36.908 --> 29:39.103
He couldn't help himself.

29:39.177 --> 29:41.611
He's the guy.
Who's the guy?

29:44.115 --> 29:47.141
Julie, we have to go right now.
Why?

29:47.218 --> 29:49.448
I can't tell you now.
Not here.
[Indistinct]

29:49.521 --> 29:51.716
But, Mom.
Do not argue with me!
G-Get your stuff now.

29:51.790 --> 29:54.953
Hey! What?
[Sighs]

29:55.026 --> 29:58.257
Look, what's going on?
She's taking Julie home.

29:58.329 --> 30:01.765
Well, why on earth
would she do that?

30:01.833 --> 30:06.099
Because I told her that you
killed Clea Vance a year ago.

30:07.806 --> 30:12.368
And I'm betting that you killed
Natasia Zorelle last night.

30:12.443 --> 30:16.812
Who else would have straightened
the clothes on Clea Vance's body?

30:16.881 --> 30:19.475
Oh, and why would I do
something like that?

30:21.753 --> 30:23.880
I would have.
Is that it?

30:23.955 --> 30:28.187
I straightened out the clothes?
[Scoffs]
I mean, that's not evidence.

30:28.259 --> 30:30.318
That-That's a hunch.

30:30.395 --> 30:34.388
That's all it is so far.

30:34.465 --> 30:37.059
You trust your instincts,
don't you?

30:37.135 --> 30:39.069
Oh, yes.

30:39.137 --> 30:42.334
And would it be the same
infallible instinct that you used...

30:42.407 --> 30:45.467
when you picked out
that jacket?

30:45.543 --> 30:49.411
Or when you did those buttons
right up to the top on your shirt,
eh?

30:49.480 --> 30:53.314
[Scoffs] What about
the evidence, Mr. Monk?

30:53.384 --> 30:56.319
What about-
You've heard of D.N.A., right?

30:56.387 --> 30:58.617
I mean, does that
ring a bell here? Hmm?

30:58.690 --> 31:01.784
D.N.A., yes.
The fibers, the hair
and the blood.

31:01.860 --> 31:06.126
They all belonged to that boy,
Pablo Ortiz, who's in jail.

31:06.197 --> 31:10.463
It couldn't have been me.
Just not possible.

31:12.237 --> 31:14.467
You're right.

31:14.539 --> 31:17.531
It's not possible.

31:17.609 --> 31:19.702
But you did it.

31:29.554 --> 31:31.613
Gordo, thanks
for getting here so fast.

31:31.689 --> 31:33.680
Sure, what's going on?
Get a load of this.

31:33.758 --> 31:37.592
Okay, there was a fashion show
upstairs in the ballroom.
I remember, last year.

31:37.662 --> 31:40.961
And one of the models,
as you know, showed up drunk.

31:41.032 --> 31:44.832
Clea Vance.
Exactly. So drunk,
according toJulian Hodge,

31:44.903 --> 31:46.894
that she almost
ruined his show.

31:46.971 --> 31:50.031
He was furious. I think
he followed her down here.

31:50.108 --> 31:52.099
They argued.
He lost control.

31:52.176 --> 31:55.634
He killed her. He beat her
to death right here.
Julian Hodge?

31:55.713 --> 31:59.843
What about the evidence?
He planted it. He framed Pablo Ortiz.

31:59.918 --> 32:02.409
Is that possible?
How could he plant
all that evidence...

32:02.487 --> 32:04.580
and clean up every
trace of himself?

32:04.656 --> 32:06.715
Actually he didn't.
He missed something.
Check this out.

32:06.791 --> 32:10.124
There was a health
inspection the day before.
They hung that flypaper in the corner.

32:10.194 --> 32:14.756
- How'd we miss it?
- We just found it this morning
behind that radiator.

32:14.832 --> 32:18.962
It must have fallen back there
during the fight. And, look, there's
three or four hairs stuck to it.

32:19.037 --> 32:22.200
And they can't be from Clea Vance
because she had long hair.

32:22.273 --> 32:26.642
They must belong toJulian Hodge,
the real killer.
This is the proof we need.

32:26.711 --> 32:28.770
How soon can you do a test
on those?
I'll get right on it.

32:28.846 --> 32:31.781
Good work.
Thanks.

32:33.117 --> 32:36.575
<i>[Cooking Timer Buzzing]</i>

32:36.654 --> 32:39.088
Honey, I think they're done!

32:43.261 --> 32:46.162
Ooh, maybe a little overdone.

32:47.999 --> 32:50.763
Julie?

32:53.071 --> 32:56.234
Honey?

33:04.148 --> 33:06.946
<i>[Cable Car Bell Ringing]</i>

33:33.678 --> 33:37.011
<i>[Man] I don't have a John Carlo, okay?</i>
<i>How many times do I have to tell you?</i>

33:37.081 --> 33:40.881
You're not on the list, all right?
Good night. Thank you.

33:41.953 --> 33:44.080
Good night!

33:45.089 --> 33:47.956
- Hello. I'm on the list.
- Name.

33:48.026 --> 33:51.120
Puff Daddy.
Plus one.

33:51.195 --> 33:53.425
This is my girlfriend.
Hi.

33:53.498 --> 33:57.594
Puff Daddy, the rapper?
Oh, no.
Not that Puff Daddy.

33:57.668 --> 34:00.136
This happens to me
all the time, doesn't it?
All the time.

34:00.204 --> 34:03.503
Yeah, let me explain.
Where to begin?

34:03.574 --> 34:06.304
All right, there
are two Puff Daddys.
Why don't you change your name?

34:06.377 --> 34:09.471
Why doesn't he change his name
is what I'm saying.

34:09.547 --> 34:11.879
I'm older than him.
I had it first.

34:11.949 --> 34:14.143
One time a lawyer told me
I could sue if l-

34:14.217 --> 34:16.914
- Look, my daughter's
in there. I'm going in.
- We gotta go in there.

34:16.987 --> 34:19.353
Hey! Hey! Hey!

34:23.161 --> 34:26.096
<i>## [Alternative]</i>

34:32.003 --> 34:33.994
<i>## [Man Singing]</i>

35:10.208 --> 35:12.676
<i>## [Continues]</i>

35:18.015 --> 35:20.813
Have you seen my daughter?

35:25.022 --> 35:28.219
Have you seen my daughter, Julie?
She's 13, long blonde hair.

35:28.292 --> 35:30.658
<i>[Julian]</i>
<i>Beautiful.</i>

35:30.728 --> 35:34.289
<i>And there's littleJulie.</i>
<i>Good. She looks very good.</i>

35:34.365 --> 35:37.391
<i>## [Continues]</i>

35:42.773 --> 35:45.367
[Gasps]
Julie!

35:47.311 --> 35:51.543
<i>Natalie, don't eat the food.</i>
<i>I just saw four models back there</i>
<i>throwing up.</i>

35:51.616 --> 35:54.414
Julie!
Miss, you can't go out there.

36:05.796 --> 36:07.991
That's not my design.
Make an announcement.

36:10.601 --> 36:12.899
[Crowd Murmuring]

36:15.339 --> 36:17.330
You cannot just run away
from me like that.

36:17.408 --> 36:19.342
You scared me to death.
Mom, come on. Mom!

36:19.410 --> 36:22.902
If we have a problem,
we need to talk about it, all right?
I thought we were partners.

36:22.980 --> 36:25.346
<i>Wait. You're embarrassing me.</i>
Get off!

36:26.417 --> 36:29.580
You said I couldn't do this,
but you don't tell me why.
What type of partner are you?

36:29.654 --> 36:32.623
Okay, I had my reasons,
all right? There are grown-up
things happening here.

36:32.690 --> 36:35.887
<i>There are dangerous things.</i>
<i>You have to trust me, honey.</i>

36:39.530 --> 36:43.022
I'm sorry.
I'm sorry too.
Oh, God.

36:43.100 --> 36:45.728
All right?
You're so grounded.

36:48.439 --> 36:53.968
<i>Listen, let's make sure that</i>
<i>the critics get lots to drink.</i>
<i>[Laughs]</i>

36:54.045 --> 36:56.843
Well, look, here's to our next
show in Milan.

36:56.914 --> 36:58.905
<i>Cinc√¨n.</i>
All the best.

36:58.983 --> 37:02.248
And congratulations. Well done.
You look stunning in that dress.

37:02.320 --> 37:06.518
<i>Fabulous.</i>
<i>It was a great show tonight.</i>
<i>Really fabulous.</i>

37:06.591 --> 37:10.220
<i>Except for that one little</i>
<i>incident with that midget.</i>

37:10.294 --> 37:12.956
<i>[Laughs]</i>
<i>That was ridiculous.</i>

37:17.268 --> 37:21.227
<i>Mmm. That's delicious,</i>
<i>isn't it? Delicious.!</i>

37:21.305 --> 37:24.433
[Laughs]
I want to get you new earrings.

37:24.508 --> 37:26.499
I want them to be drops.

37:26.577 --> 37:30.809
Oh, look what the cat dragged in.
You know, you nearly ruined my show.

37:30.881 --> 37:32.974
You nearly ruined my daughter.
Hmm.

37:33.050 --> 37:35.041
- Mr. Hodge, hello.
- Oh, hello.

37:35.119 --> 37:37.246
<i>Great party.</i>
Thank you.

37:37.321 --> 37:39.915
There's somebody here I'd really
love for you to meet.
There he is.

37:39.991 --> 37:42.084
<i>Oh? Now?</i>
<i>[Stottlemeyer]</i>
<i>Come on.</i>

37:42.159 --> 37:44.320
Oh, yeah.
Can't it wait?

37:44.395 --> 37:46.693
No, no, no.
He's very important.

37:49.967 --> 37:52.993
Julian Hodge, I'd like you
to meet Howard Gordon.

37:53.070 --> 37:56.301
Howard is one of our
forensic experts.
Oh. How do you do?

37:56.374 --> 38:00.174
He's been examining some
evidence that we just uncovered
in the Clea Vance case.

38:00.244 --> 38:02.269
What, new evidence?

38:02.346 --> 38:05.144
That's right.
Four strands of human hair found
at the scene of the crime.

38:05.216 --> 38:07.446
For the record, Gordo,
is this your report?

38:07.518 --> 38:10.043
For the record, yes, it is.
Uh-huh.

38:10.121 --> 38:13.522
- And you examined these hair samples
that we found earlier today?
- <i>I did.</i>

38:13.591 --> 38:18.619
- And were you able to match these
hairs to any individual?
- <i>Yes, sir.</i>

38:18.696 --> 38:22.291
- And for the record, who do
these hairs belong to?
- Pablo Ortiz.

38:22.366 --> 38:26.860
Ortiz? Isn't that the boy who's
already in jail for the murder?

38:26.937 --> 38:30.737
[Laughs]
Well, I think, gentlemen,
we're finished here.

38:30.808 --> 38:32.867
Don't mind if I get back
to my party?

38:32.943 --> 38:35.707
Hang on. Hang on.

38:35.780 --> 38:37.805
Gordo, I'm sorry,
but you're under arrest.

38:37.882 --> 38:41.750
Accessory to murder
and falsifying evidence.
What?

38:41.819 --> 38:44.754
Here's what I couldn't
figure out.

38:44.822 --> 38:47.586
If you were guilty, how
could all the evidence
point somewhere else?

38:47.658 --> 38:50.559
There could be only
one possible answer.

38:50.628 --> 38:52.892
There was something wrong
with the evidence.

38:52.963 --> 38:58.128
<i>We did some digging, Gordo.</i>
<i>You did make a lot of money this year,</i>
<i>but it wasn't in real estate.</i>

38:58.202 --> 39:00.261
Here's what happened.

39:00.338 --> 39:03.535
<i>When you did the forensic work</i>
<i>on the Clea Vance murder,</i>

39:03.607 --> 39:08.237
<i>you realized all the evidence</i>
<i>pointed toJulian Hodge.</i>

39:08.312 --> 39:11.543
<i>You decided to cash in.</i>

39:11.615 --> 39:14.516
<i>You made Hodge an offer</i>
<i>he was in no position to refuse.</i>

39:14.585 --> 39:17.713
<i>For a price, you'd bury</i>
<i>the evidence against him.</i>

39:17.788 --> 39:21.280
<i>There was only one problem.</i>

39:21.359 --> 39:24.817
You had to close the case.
You needed a fall guy.

39:24.895 --> 39:27.830
Hodge remembered a young
delivery boy named Pablo Ortiz,

39:27.898 --> 39:29.889
a poor kid, barely spoke
any English.

39:29.967 --> 39:31.958
He was a perfect patsy.

39:32.036 --> 39:35.062
Hodge got Natasia to help him.
She called the police...

39:35.139 --> 39:37.869
and accused Ortiz
of stalking her roommate.

39:37.942 --> 39:40.376
<i>The police arrested Pablo.</i>

39:40.444 --> 39:43.242
<i>They took hair and blood samples</i>
<i>and sent them to you</i>- 

39:43.314 --> 39:45.578
<i>And the rest was easy.</i>

39:45.649 --> 39:48.516
<i>All you had to do</i>
<i>was re-label them.</i>

39:51.989 --> 39:54.321
- Pablo never had a chance.
- You can't prove any of this.

39:54.392 --> 39:57.452
We don't have to.
You proved it for us
five minutes ago...

39:57.528 --> 40:02.227
when you swore that these hair samples
belonged to Pablo Ortiz.

40:02.299 --> 40:04.767
So you planted that hair
to test him?

40:04.835 --> 40:07.633
Well, yeah.

40:07.705 --> 40:10.936
Whose hair was it?
It was mine.

40:11.008 --> 40:13.806
Natalie pulled it out
with a tweezer.
She just yanked it out.

40:13.878 --> 40:16.506
What was I supposed to do?
You could have cut them
like I told you to.

40:16.580 --> 40:18.912
We needed the follicles.
No, we didn't need the follicles...

40:18.983 --> 40:21.577
because we knew he wasn't
going to test anything.

40:21.652 --> 40:24.621
That was the whole point.
It's embarrassing.
Okay, don't be such a baby.

40:24.688 --> 40:26.781
Hang on. Hang on!

40:26.857 --> 40:30.315
I forgot what we were doing.
Oh, yeah, we're arresting you two.

40:30.394 --> 40:33.830
You know the drill, Gordo.

40:35.833 --> 40:37.994
So, it's true what they say, huh?

40:38.068 --> 40:40.969
You can never judge a person
by how they dress.

40:41.038 --> 40:44.496
Well, you know what?
Let me tell you what
you're gonna be wearing.

40:44.575 --> 40:46.907
I hope you like orange.
It's a little jumpsuit thing.

40:46.977 --> 40:49.537
It has a number right here.
You can wear it anywhere, really-

40:49.613 --> 40:51.706
Indoors, walking around the yard-

40:58.923 --> 41:02.381
[Sobbing]

41:02.460 --> 41:05.952
[Speaking Spanish]

41:06.030 --> 41:09.659
[Gate Buzzer Buzzes]
Mama.

41:11.936 --> 41:16.532
Thank you, Mr, Monk.
How can I repay you,
Mr. Monk?

41:16.607 --> 41:21.601
I have no money.
Now that you mention it,
it is only 2:30.

41:21.679 --> 41:26.742
If we left now, you could be
back at work at 3:15,
put in a couple of hours,

41:26.817 --> 41:29.377
inspect, what, 90,
maybe a hundred shirts.

41:29.453 --> 41:33.583
But I took the day off.
No, no, no, no.
You don't wanna do that.

41:33.657 --> 41:37.388
No. You're Inspector Number 8.
You have a lot of people
depending on you.

41:37.461 --> 41:40.521
Mr. Monk, I'm sure
they would like to visit.
You know? Catch up.

41:40.598 --> 41:44.534
Yeah, there's plenty of time
for that. They got the whole
weekend for that.

41:44.602 --> 41:46.536
Unless you wanna work
on Saturday.

41:46.604 --> 41:49.300
[Speaking Spanish] Saturday?
[Speaks Spanish]

